column3: Concept ACK.\n\nAlso it will make the `make deploy` [bug](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/20422#issuecomment-919012839) on macOS 10.14.6 outdated :)
> Also it will make the make deploy bug on macOS 10.14.6 outdated :)\n\nI've commented on that PR. Given what you've posted it's not exactly clear that is a bug.
There was an odd native windows CI failure, which I re-ran: https://cirrus-ci.com/task/6041484689408000

> There was an odd native windows CI failure, which I re-ran: https://cirrus-ci.com/task/6041484689408000

It's a network failure
```
https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/releases/download/v7.1.0/PowerShell-7.1.0-win-x86.zip: WinHttpReceiveResponse() failed: 12030
```
which happens sometimes.

Welcome to the yearly MacOSX bump :smile: \nI guess that's a fact of life, Apple is kind of harsh with regard to backward/forward compatibility (so many quasi-arbitrary changes every release, no beginning in trying to support all combinationsâ€¦), and besides, MacOS users don't seem to mind.\nConcept ACK.
